The paper discusses the use of formal methods in the development of high-assurance separation kernels, which are used in critical domains such as avionics/aerospace, military/defense, and medical devices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), software engineering (cs.SE), operating systems (cs.OS), programming languages (cs.PL), and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
